  "body": "### Description of Issue\r\nTransaction from Ledger wallet with specific DATA contents results in \"incorrect\" transaction with wrong \"From\" address and thus transactions fails with error claiming that there are not enough funds.\r\n\r\nData causing this error:\r\\r\n\r\nProblems seems to happen only in Google Chrome. Brave browser and Opera didn't have the problem. Reproduced with 2 different Ledger initialized with different seeds.\r\n\r\n### What exactly were you doing when you encountered this issue?\r\nTrying to send ETH to a contract with specific data.\r\n\r\n\r\n### How were you accessing your wallet?\r\nLedger Nano S (Firmware 1.4.2, MCU 1.6)\r\n\r\n### Description of Your Machine\r\n\r\n- Browser: Google Chrome\r\n- Browser version: Version 73.0.3683.103 (Official Build) (64-bit)\r\n- Operating system: Windows 10 (version 1803)\r\n- Device: Reproduced on 2 different PCs\r\n- MyCrypto.com\r\n\r\n\r\n### Console Logs / Screenshots\r\n![mcr3](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1264210/55676417-475bfd00-58d5-11e9-961f-7a9b64395992.png)\r\n![mcr4](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/1264210/55676419-4c20b100-58d5-11e9-97d9-a7f4f28e9eab.png)",
